  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do l see who viewed my videos on Instagram?",
  "response": "Viewing who has watched your videos on Instagram depends on the type of video you've posted. Here's a breakdown of how you can see viewers for different kinds of Instagram videos:\n\n### 1. **Instagram Stories**\nInstagram Stories are temporary posts that disappear after 24 hours. You can see exactly who has viewed your Story by following these steps:\n\n1. **Open Instagram:** Launch the Instagram app on your mobile device.\n2. **Go to Your Story:** Tap your profile picture at the top of your feed or swipe right from the home screen to access your Story.\n3. **View the Viewer List:** While your Story is playing, swipe up on the screen. A list of usernames who have viewed your Story will appear.\n\n### 2. **Instagram Reels**\nReels are short, engaging videos that can reach a wider audience. As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, here's what you can and cannot do regarding viewing who watched your Reels:\n\n- **Basic Accounts:**\n  - **View Count:** You can see how many times your Reel has been viewed.\n  - **Likes and Comments:** You can see who has liked or commented on your Reel.\n  - **Limited Viewer Info:** Unlike Stories, Instagram does not provide a detailed list of who has viewed your Reel.\n\n- **Creator or Business Accounts:**\n  - **Insights:** If you switch to a Creator or Business account, you gain access to more detailed analytics, including demographic information about your viewers (age, gender, location) but not individual usernames.\n  - **How to Switch:**\n    - Go to your profile and tap the three lines (\u2261) in the top-right corner.\n    - Select **Settings** > **Account** > **Switch to Professional Account** and follow the prompts.\n\n### 3. **Regular Video Posts (Feed Videos)**\nFor videos posted to your Instagram feed:\n\n- **View Count:** You can see the total number of views your video has received.\n- **Likes and Comments:** You can view who has liked or commented on your video.\n- **No Viewer List:** Instagram does **not** provide a list of individual users who have viewed your regular feed videos.\n\n### 4. **Instagram Live**\nIf you use Instagram Live to stream videos in real-time:\n\n- **Viewers List:** You can see who is watching your live broadcast in real-time.\n- **After the Live Session:** If you save the live video to your IGTV (now called **Instagram Video**), it may show aggregated view counts, but not individual viewers.\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n\n- **Privacy Settings:** Ensure your account's privacy settings are configured according to your preferences. A private account restricts your content visibility to approved followers only.\n  \n- **Third-Party Apps:** Be cautious of third-party apps or services that claim to show you who viewed your Instagram videos. These can violate Instagram's terms of service and may compromise your account's security.\n\n- **Regular Updates:** Instagram frequently updates its features. To stay informed about the latest tools and capabilities, consider following Instagram's [official blog](https://about.instagram.com/blog/) or their [Help Center](https://help.instagram.com/).\n\n### **Summary**\n\n- **Stories:** You can see exactly who viewed each Story.\n- **Reels:** Limited viewer information; detailed analytics available for Creator/Business accounts but not individual usernames.\n- **Feed Videos:** Only view counts and engagement (likes/comments) are visible; individual viewers are not listed.\n- **Live Videos:** Real-time viewer list during the live session.\n\nIf you're looking to engage more with your audience, consider using features like Stories and Live broadcasts, where you can directly see and interact with your viewers.",
